The paper focuses on designing an interface for collaborative crime analysis, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and human-centered computing (HCC) aspects. Therefore, cs.HC is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to distributed collaboration, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (computers and society). The paper discusses crime analysis, which involves security and privacy concerns, making cs.CR (cryptography and security) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and sensemaking, which are relevant to cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
